    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n**Refer to Strategy 1 and 3**\r\n\r\n1. Run the code and compare the output to the comments describing what should be happening. Take note of any unexpected behavior.\r\n2. *Identify what might be causing the issue. Consider what is happening differently than expected.*\r\n2. Since there is no error message, use AI Tutor to help analyze your code and find the bug. Ask for debugging advice or explanations of why the code isn't behaving as expected.\r\n3. Modify the code to fix the issue.\r\n\t- **Hint:** Focus on checking the logic of your code rather than just syntax errors!\r\n    \r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**🔎 Show me how**]\r\nThere could be several ways to fix this bug! In programming solutions can look different. Here is one way to get the code to function properly:\r\n\r\nTo enlarge the code drag out the side bar of the instruction box.\r\n![](https://images.code.org/783334016131df64ccdfc38934d0a352-image-1743523114653.png)\r\n:::\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# create two painter objects\nsusan = Painter()\njoe = Painter()\n\n# turn right by turning left 3x\n# takes an object name as the parameter\ndef turn_right(painter):\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n\n# paints a continuous line as it moves\ndef paint_line(painter):\n  painter.move()\n  painter.take_paint()\n  painter.paint(\"blue\")\n  painter.move()\n\n# object susan will paint the top horizontal grid line, from the first square to the last square\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\n\n# object joe will turn right and paint the left vertical grid line, from the first square to the last square\nturn_right(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\n\n# Expected outcome: the top line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n# Expected outcome: the left line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
